casebody.data:
MAX LOMACHINSKY, PLAINTIFF-APPELLEE, v. LOUIS APRIL, DEFENDANT-APPELLANT. Submitted December 21, 1922 Decided February 20, 1923.

Before Justices Parker, Bergen and Minturn.

*4Per Curiam.

This case was marked to be submitted on briefs. There is no brief for the respondent, Eor the appellant, a brief is submitted, but the same is not signed by a counselor of this court. It is signed in the name of an attorney-at-law who is not a counselor. Such a brief, under the established practice, will not be considered, and the appeal will be dismissed. Hazard v. Phœnix Woodworking Co., 78 N. J. Eq. 568.
